### Register a new simulated node
POST http://localhost:3000/api/nodes/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ownerName": "John Doe",
  "nodeName": "Test Security Node",
  "nodeType": "FIELD"
}

### Send telemetry payload to an ESP32 node
# IMPORTANT: Replace the x-device-id and x-api-key headers 
# with actual values returned from the internal DB!
# Since we seeded `eco_node_warehouse_dev` via Prisma Seed, we can use it:
POST http://localhost:3000/api/telemetry
Content-Type: application/json
x-device-id: eco_node_warehouse_dev
x-api-key: eco_sk_warehouse_dev_123

{
  "internal_temp_c": 28.5,
  "internal_pressure_hpa": 1002,
  "external_temp_c": 32.1,
  "fan_active": true,
  "pump_active": false
}

### Verify Latest Cache
GET http://localhost:3000/api/nodes/latest

### Verify Historical Telemetry Map
# Fetch the dynamically seeded warehouse node from the DB ID
# (Replace the slug with an actual cuid if calling via curl)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/nodes/storage_hub_1/telemetry?limit=10
